  "question": "How can stateless persons, refugees, and foreigners apply for a travel document in Belgium?",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "In Belgium, stateless persons, recognized refugees, and foreigners who cannot obtain a national passport from their home country can apply for a Belgian travel document at the municipality where they reside. This document serves as a substitute for a national passport."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Conditions\n**For Recognized Refugees and Stateless Persons:**\n- Possession of valid residence documents.\n\n**For Other Foreigners:**\n- Proof of meeting specific conditions as determined by the Federal Public Service (FPS) Foreign Affairs."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Procedure\n**For Recognized Refugees or Stateless Persons:**\n- Submit the application directly to your municipal authority.\n- Provide valid identity documents and a recent passport photo (maximum six months old).\n- If your documents and status are in order, the municipality will process your application immediately.\n\n**For Foreigners (Not Recognized as Refugees or Stateless Persons):**\n1. Obtain permission from the FPS Foreign Affairs before applying at your municipality.\n2. Use the FPS Foreign Affairs website to check eligibility and required documents.\n3. Submit your request to:\n   - Email: passeport@diplobel.fed.be with the subject “Application for a Travel Document for a Foreigner.”\n   - Postal Address: \n     FOD Buitenlandse Zaken, \n     Directie Reis- en identiteitsdocumenten,\n     Dienst C2.2 Individuele dossiers & nationale regelgeving,\n     Karmelietenstraat 15, 1000 Brussel.\n4. Include the following in your email or letter:\n   - Full name and first names.\n   - Place of birth.\n   - Nationality.\n   - Copy of your residence permit.\n   - Any other relevant documents.\n5. For minors, applications must be submitted by parents or guardians.\n6. The investigation takes approximately six weeks. Once permission is granted, submit your application within two weeks to the municipality, along with identity documents and a recent passport photo."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Required Documents\n**For Recognized Refugees or Stateless Persons:**\n- Residence permit (e.g., card A, B, C, D, F(+)). For children under 12, an identity card for minors is required.\n- A recent passport photo (maximum six months old).\n\n**For Foreigners (Not Recognized as Refugees or Stateless Persons):**\n- Relevant identity documents depending on the situation.\n- A recent passport photo (maximum six months old)."
    },
    {
      "type": "source",
      "url": "https://www.belgium.be/en"
    }
