  "content": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If you lose your identity card, passport, residence permit, or bank card in Belgium, it is crucial to take immediate steps to prevent fraud and secure your information. Belgium provides dedicated services to assist in such cases, including DOCSTOP and Card Stop."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Lost or Stolen Identity Document\n**Steps to Follow:**\n- **Report to DOCSTOP:**\n  - Call DOCSTOP at **00800 2123 2123** (free) to block your document.\n  - If the free number is inaccessible, call **+32 2 518 2123**.\n- **In Case of Theft:**\n  - Notify DOCSTOP immediately.\n  - File a theft report at the nearest police station or local police office.\n- **In Case of Loss:**\n  - Notify DOCSTOP immediately.\n  - Report the loss at your municipality. If outside office hours, visit the police station for a temporary certificate.\n- **Special Cases for Residence Permits:**\n  - File a loss report at the police before going to the municipality.\n\n**When Abroad:**\n- Follow the same steps: notify DOCSTOP and the nearest police station.\n- For a temporary identity document, contact the Belgian consulate."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Important Note on Found Documents\nOnce reported as lost or stolen, identity documents (e.g., passports, eIDs) are no longer valid, even if found later. Using a flagged document could result in denial of entry to foreign countries or immediate return to Belgium. Destroy the document at your municipality and apply for a replacement."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Lost or Stolen Bank Card\n**Steps to Follow:**\n- Call **Card Stop** at **078 170 170** to block your card immediately.\n  - From abroad, call **+32 78 170 170** (international rates apply).\n  - Card Stop operates 24/7 and charges no fees for blocking your card; only call charges apply.\n- Card Stop blocks:\n  - Bank cards.\n  - Credit cards.\n  - Fuel cards.\n  - Electronic checks."
