  "question": "How can you obtain an Apostille for a document in Belgium?",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "An Apostille is an official certification that verifies the authenticity of a document for international use. This system, established by the 1961 Hague Apostille Convention, allows official documents to be recognized in other member countries."
    },
    {
                      "type": "image",
                      "url": "https://diplomatie.belgium.be/sites/default/files/2022-03/l%C3%A9galisation%20de%20documents.jpeg"
             },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### What is an Apostille?\n- An Apostille is a certification issued by the competent authority of a country to verify the authenticity of a document.\n- It confirms that the document is genuine and issued by the designated authority.\n- Apostilles are valid only between countries that are parties to the Hague Apostille Convention."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Why is an Apostille Needed?\nApostille certification is required when official documents need international recognition. Examples include:\n- **Educational Documents:** Diplomas, transcripts, certificates.\n- **Civil Status Documents:** Birth certificates, marriage certificates, death certificates.\n- **Judicial Documents:** Criminal record checks.\n- **Notarized Documents:** Powers of attorney, contracts, declarations.\n- **Commercial Documents:** Company formation documents, tax records."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### How to Obtain an Apostille in Belgium?\n**1. Prepare the Document:**\n- Ensure the document is original and official. Notarization may be required for certain documents.\n\n**2. Identify the Competent Authority:**\n- Judicial documents: **Courts**.\n- Notarized documents: **Ministry of Justice**.\n- Official documents: **Ministry of Foreign Affairs**.\n\n**3. Submit the Application:**\n- Apply to the appropriate authority for the Apostille.\n- Pay the required fee.\n\n**4. Collect the Document:**\n- Once the process is complete, retrieve the document with the Apostille certification."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "### Importance of Apostille in Belgium\n- Facilitates the international recognition of documents.\n- Commonly required for immigration, education, job applications, or marriage abroad.\n- Without an Apostille, additional verification may be required to use the document in another country."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "For guidance on the appropriate steps and authorities, contact the consulate of the country where the document will be used or consult Belgian authorities."
    },
    {
      "type": "source",
      "url": "https://elegalisation.diplomatie.be/"
